## 📦 Installation

### 1. Clone repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/data-sentinel.git
cd data-sentinel
2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv

# Windows
.venv\Scripts\activate
3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
4. Configure environment

Create .env file:

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/datasentinel
5. Run backend
uvicorn backend.app.main:app --reload

Backend:
http://127.0.0.1:8000

Docs:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs

6. Run frontend
streamlit run frontend/dashboard.py

Frontend:
http://localhost:8501

📡 API Endpoints
| Method | Endpoint               | Description                      |
| ------ | ---------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| POST   | `/upload-csv`          | Upload dataset + generate report |
| GET    | `/reports`             | Fetch all reports                |
| GET    | `/reports/{id}`        | Fetch single report              |
| GET    | `/reports/{id}/status` | AI processing status             |

🔐 Design Principles
AI is non-blocking by design
System works fully without OpenAI
NumPy → JSON normalization enforced
Background AI processing (async worker)
Fault-tolerant API design
📌 Roadmap
KL-divergence drift scoring
Real-time streaming ingestion
Authentication system (JWT)
Dataset comparison UI
Scheduled monitoring jobs
Export reports (PDF / CSV)
